{"lemma":"سَيْلُ","slug":"سَيْلُ","root":"س.#.ل","root_slug":"س-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/س-_-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَيْل","root":"سيل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n21461"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَالَ (sāla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flood, stream, torrent","examples":[{"text":"أَنزَلَ مِنَ ٱلسَّمَاءِ مَاءً فَسَالَتْ أَوْدِيَةٌ بِقَدَرِهَا فَٱحْتَمَلَ ٱلسَّيْلُ زَبَدًا رَابِيًا","english":"He has sent down water from the sky so the valleys flow, [each valley] according to its measure, so then the torrent bears a rising foam …"},{"text":"تأمل هنالك انى حصدت رؤوس الورى و زهور الأمل\nو رويت بالدم قلب التراب و اشربته الدمع حتى ثمل\nســيجرفك الســيل ، سيل الدماء\nو يأكلك العاصف المشتعل","english":"Consider there, that where you have sowed the heads of man and the flowers of hope\nAnd drenched with blood, the heart of the soil and watered it with tears till drunk\nYou'll be swept by the stream, the torrent of blood\nAnd the windy flame will devour you."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sajl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21461","headword_ar":"سَيْلٌ","root":"syl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A torrent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flow of water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection of rainwater,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a valley,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water-course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"torrent-bed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water that comes to one"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from rain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in any case, or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from rain that has not fallen upon one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) originally an inf. n.: (Msb, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suyuwlN","text_ar":"سُيُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, Msb, K:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAy^ilapN","text_ar":"سَايِلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayolN","text_ar":"سَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAy^ilu","text_ar":"سَوَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. in the M as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running, waters"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And they said also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N sayolN","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ سَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAy^ilN","text_ar":"سَايِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Flowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running, water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M, K;) putting the inf. n. in the place of the epithet. (M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajadotu baqolFA wabuqayolFA wamaA='F EalalFA sayolFA","text_ar":"وَجَدْتُ بَقْلًا وَبُقَيْلًا وَمَا=ءً عَلَلًا سَيْلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I found herbs full-grown and large and tall, and herbs not full-grown and therefore small,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and water among trees, flowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a saying of one sent to seek for herbage and water; mentioned by Th. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","Msb","TA","S"]}]}}